{
  "texts": [
    "Note that the optimization with respect to λ is a little more problematic when π is not uniform, because the optimal λ would depend on the data, which is not allowed -at the moment.",
    "We will come back to the choice of λ in the general case soon.",
    "Let us also consider the statement of Theorem 2.1 in this case.",
    "With probability at least 1 -δ, we have:",
    "As the bound holds for all ρ ∈ P(Θ), it holds in particular for all ρ in the set of Dirac masses {δ θ, θ ∈ Θ}."
  ]
